last_episode_to_air.name: My Brother's Keeper
last_episode_to_air.overview: Lyle takes over the responsibilities at a Ranger's Station when Dodo's misreading of a holiday brochure leads them to an abandoned park.

name: Animal Crackers
overview: The Animal Crackers is a 1997 television series produced by Cinar, and association with Alphanim, about a group of animals that live in a fictional jungle called Freeborn. It is based on the comic strip Animal Crackers. The show aired in the United States on Fox Family in 1998 and the Cookie Jar Toons block on This TV from November 2008 to August 2009.

episodes.name: High-Gnu'n
episodes.overview: Rowland the water-buffalo challenges Gnu for the leadership of the herd. After doing everything he can to avoid a confrontation, Gnu finally decides to stand up for himself.

episodes.name: Eu-Genial
episodes.overview: Eugene decides to turn over a new leaf and actually be ""nice"" for a change. Unfortunately, his misguided attempts at performing good deeds, ends up causing even more pain and suffering

episodes.name: Dino-Sore-As-Heck
episodes.overview: Lyle discovers a perfectly preserved dinosaur skeleton and decides to impress Lana with his amazing find. Meanwhile, the rest of the gang attempts to reconstruct what they believe to be an early ancestor of Dodo's.

episodes.name: Wilderness Training
episodes.overview: Gnu becomes volunteer scout leader to c-squad, the most unorganized, accident-prone, inefficient bunch of young wilderness scouts in training. Gnu's task is made all the more difficult by the late addition of an eager new recruit: Eugene.

episodes.name: Treasure of the Preserva Freeborna
episodes.overview: It's Indiana Jones meets Looney Toons as Dodo, Lyle, and Tito the chameleon journey off in search of a legendary treasure.

episodes.name: Call Waiting
episodes.overview: It's Twister meets that movie where a bunch of people fight over something when an act of nature deposits a shiny new phone booth smack-dab in the heart of the Preserve.

episodes.name: Goodness Snakes
episodes.overview: Lyle is bitten by a snake who doesn't know whether she is poisonous or not. Assuming the worst, Lyle milks his impending doom for all it's worth.

episodes.name: Meat the Folks
episodes.overview: When her parents come to visit, Lana drafts Lyle into pretending he is her boyfriend. But when mom and dad want a test of their future son-in-law's hunting skills, Lyle has to convince Gnu to play along.

episodes.name: If You Can't Be'Em, Join'Em
episodes.overview: Dodo uses hypnosis to help Eugene overcome his fear of mice. The session works well - in fact, a little too well and Eugene becomes convinced that he is, in fact, a mouse.

episodes.name: Spring Fever
episodes.overview: Lyle, Gnu, Dodo, and Tito the chameleon are smitten with spring fever and go all-out in their attempts to woo Lana. Dodo, meanwhile, suffering from amnesia, sweeps through the preserve as a mysterious, masked romancer.

episodes.name: Pachyderm Pandemonium
episodes.overview: Eugene is thrilled to hear that the Loyal Order of Rogue Elephants has chosen Freeborn as the location for its next convention. But when his old buddy Ralph drops by for an early visit, trouble brews. This jungle ain't big enough for two bullies.

episodes.name: Herd Mentality
episodes.overview: In their eagerness to win the annual Better Herds and Flocks competition, the herd dumps Gnu for a more resilient leader: Eugene.

episodes.name: Going Quackers
episodes.overview: After reading a book entitled ""Odd and Doubtful Birds of Africa"", Dodo becomes convinced that he is really a duck.

episodes.name: Blockbusted
episodes.overview: After viewing a tourist video of their daily lives, the gang ""borrows"" the camera in an attempt to reshoot the film to their liking.

episodes.name: Pachyn my Bags
episodes.overview: Irked by the rest of the preserve's lack of respect for him, Eugene packs his bags and leaves Freeborn...to the delight of everyone else.

episodes.name: Mommy Dearest
episodes.overview: A baby bird imprints itself on Eugene. Despite the elephant's most creative efforts, he just can't seem to shake the little guy.

episodes.name: Sherlock Dodo
episodes.overview: When Lyle mysteriously disappears, everyone assumes the worst...and Sherlock Dodo is on the case.

episodes.name: Poultrygeist
episodes.overview: When things begin to mysteriously disappear from the preserve, the animals organize a neighbourhood watch. But they soon suspect that they are dealing with a ghostly presence.

episodes.name: Lyle's Psychic Alliance
episodes.overview: When a couple of off-hand predictions come true, Lyle opens up his own psychic network.

episodes.name: Snowed Inn
episodes.overview: The preserve is hit by a drought and Lyle takes it upon himself to enact an ancient ceremonial rain dance. But instead of bringing rain, he causes it to snow. As the entire preserve falls under a snowy spell, Lyle works feverishly to reverse the incantation.

episodes.name: Svelte Veldt
episodes.overview: Eugene decides to diet and appoints Gnu as his personal trainer. But when his diet and exercise program becomes a little too taxing, Eugene decides that misery loves company and orders the rest of the preserve to join him on his get-fit plan.

episodes.name: All the Preserve's a Stage
episodes.overview: The gang stages their own version of Romeo and Juliet in commemoration of Freeborn's 100th anniversary.

episodes.name: It's a Date
episodes.overview: Frustrated by his inability to get anywhere with Lana, Lyle resorts to a dating service.

episodes.name: Bully for Woolly
episodes.overview: When the gang defrosts a centuries-old Woolly Mammoth, the prehistoric pachyderm becomes the hottest thing to hit Freeborn since pizza pockets. As Woolly Fever sweeps through the preserve, Lyle is left to wonder ""What the heck is going on here?""

episodes.name: Lights! Camera! Lyle!
episodes.overview: Lyle enlists the aid of famed gecko director Sidney Vanderlaffderlanger to help him win Lana's heart

episodes.name: Bud and Edna's Excellent Adventure!
episodes.overview: When near-sighted tourists Bud and Edna Farkle set up camp on the Preserve, the gang comes up with some ""creative"" ways to rid themselves of the unwanted guests.

episodes.name: Sleepover
episodes.overview: Eugene can't sleep, and decides no one else can. What he calls a sleepover is really an invitation to entertain him all night.

episodes.name: Classified Casanova
episodes.overview: Gnu uses the classifieds to find a true love match. Things don't work out the way he'd hoped when Eugene turns out to be his surprise date.

episodes.name: Eight Hooves Out
episodes.overview: Dodo gets his friends in way over their heads when he accepts a challenge to a baseball game from the All-Star monkeys. Especially when Eugene, the Babe Ruth of Freeborn, would rather do anything else.

episodes.name: My Brother's Keeper
episodes.overview: Lyle takes over the responsibilities at a Ranger's Station when Dodo's misreading of a holiday brochure leads them to an abandoned park.

episodes.name: Lyle's Ark
episodes.overview: Everyone ignores Lyle's warnings of an impending monsoon, and the good-hearted lion ends up building an ark with room enough for everyone â€” but him.

episodes.name: How To Be a Millionare
episodes.overview: When news spreads about Lyle's inheritance, the lion becomes very popular as everybody starts manoeuvring for a piece of the riches.

episodes.name: Lyle Files
episodes.overview: A firefly caught in the lens of Lyle's telescope has all of Freeborn believing in flying saucers.

episodes.name: The Butler Did It
episodes.overview: After the gang convinces Eugene that Dodo saved his life, the pachyderm reluctantly agrees to become his butler. When Eugene finds out the truth, everyone pays.

episodes.name: Lyle in the Fast Lane
episodes.overview: Lana shows appreciation for hard-partying monkeys, provoking a misguided Lyle to steal a jeep and take the gang for a joyride.

episodes.name: A Wing and a Prayer
episodes.overview: When Dodo tries to take advantage of a money-back guarantee, he accidently attracts the Godfather of vultures to the Preserve.

episodes.name: Schooldaze
episodes.overview: Much to their horror, our gang of regulars is invited to a Class Reunion.

episodes.name: Call of the Wild
episodes.overview: Dodo, upset with how domesticated the Freeborn animals have become, arranges a return-to-nature expedition -- portable TV and all.

episodes.name: The Cold Shoulder
episodes.overview: Lyle returns from meditating with Tibetan monks and tries to force his quacky ideas on a flu-ridden Freeborn. Thanks to Lyle's tireless efforts, everyone gets worse.

episodes.name: The Last Dodo Egg
episodes.overview: When Dodo believes he's laid the last Dodo egg, he treats it with all the reverence the event implies. Eugene just wants to eat it.

episodes.name: Lana Turner Overdrive
episodes.overview: Lana's had it with Lyle's constant pestering for a date, but when her efforts to chase him off works, she misses him.

episodes.name: Trust Me
episodes.overview: The past comes back to haunt Lana when a Trust Councillor she hires turns out to be someone she slighted in school.

episodes.name: Birthday Palooza
episodes.overview: No one throws a surprise birthday party like Lyle, except it's HIS birthday. He's got to get the idea into someone else's head before it's too late.

episodes.name: Tito in Love
episodes.overview: A female chameleon moves to Freeborn, and Tito is smitten. With the help of his friends, his chances of capturing her tiny heart becomes next to none.

episodes.name: Downsizing
episodes.overview: Dodo misunderstands a news report and sets all of Freeborn competing to prove their 'worth' to the community before being turfed out.

episodes.name: Gnus in Canoes
episodes.overview: When Gnu sets off on a father/son adventure with Jr., the last thing he expects is to be joined by Lyle and Dodo.

episodes.name: Beauty and Eugene
episodes.overview: The biggest star in the world is an elephant named Ella, and when her show makes a pit stop in Freeborn, Eugene does everything he can to capture her heart.

episodes.name: Freeborn for Rent
episodes.overview: J.P. Weasel manages to turn Freeborn into a tourist trap with Eugene the Mad Elephant as its main attraction.

episodes.name: Horrorscope
episodes.overview: When Eugene becomes a devout follower of his daily horoscope, all of Freeborn pays the price.

episodes.name: Lights! Camera! Gnu!
episodes.overview: When a film director, famed for turning nobodies into big name stars, arrives in Freeborn for some R&R, Gnu sees it as an opportunity to find a new career path. Unfortunately, Gnu is lacking in that one quality the director desperately needs -- talent.

episodes.name: Loony Bin
episodes.overview: A bird arrives believing he's Dodo's cousin. Much to Dodo's dismay, everyone falls for the loony imposter.

episodes.name: That's What Friends are For
episodes.overview: Lyle and Dodo's friendship is tested when a piece of clothing proves more popular than the both of them.

episodes.name: Look Who's Not Talking
episodes.overview: Lyle gets to play Uncle to his little nephew Louie, with all the expected, and disastrous results.

episodes.name: Paris, Freeborn
episodes.overview: Lyle, just back from a trip to France, tries to instill some Parisian manners on his less than enthusiastic Freeborn friends.

episodes.name: Eugenius
episodes.overview: Eugene is struck by lightning, provoking two startling changes; One, he's getting smarter in leaps and bounds. And two, he's become the largest magnet in the world!

episodes.name: Citizen Eugene
episodes.overview: Eugene decides to publish a quality Freeborn newspaper which quickly deteriorates into a tabloid.

episodes.name: Dial-A-Phobia
episodes.overview: A local radio shock-jock convinces the Freeborn community that EVERYBODY has a phobia!

episodes.name: Time Flies but Dodo Doesn't
episodes.overview: Dodo bangs his noggin' and travels back to prehistoric times when dodo birds were a dime a dozen.

episodes.name: A Rumour of Her Own
episodes.overview: Lana decides to prove how gullible everyone is by starting a ridiculous rumour. Problem is, everything she makes up keeps coming true!

episodes.name: Prime Time Crime
episodes.overview: Dodo is everybody's best friend when they discover he has illegal cable. That is, until the cable police start asking questions, and the gang disappears.

episodes.name: Dustbusters
episodes.overview: The gang believes unless they clean up their act, and Freeborn, they'll be sent packing by the Park Ranger.

episodes.name: Freeborn Online
episodes.overview: Dodo discovers that ANYTHING can be bought online, provoking a Freeborn-wide buying spree. Then, the bill arrives.

episodes.name: Stop in the Name of Lana
episodes.overview: Lana replaces Eugene as the Freeborn Sheriff, and surprises everyone with her power-mad enthusiasm for the job.

episodes.name: Starstruck
episodes.overview: When a meteor crashes into Lyle's cave, everyone goes looking for aliens. Soon, EVERYONE looks suspicious.

episodes.name: Volcano Madness
episodes.overview: The rumbling of a nearby volcano provokes the gang to come up with Freeborn-saving solutions, each more ridiculous than the last.

episodes.name: Love is Blind
episodes.overview: A very lonely Dodo mistakes a plastic dodo as the real thing, and falls in love.

episodes.name: Wishing Well
episodes.overview: When Gnu accidently empties a wishing well of all its coins, he takes it onto himself to see to it that everyone's wishes still come true.

episodes.name: Eu've Got Mail
episodes.overview: Eugene refuses to respond to a chain letter, setting off a string of comical consequences.

episodes.name: Message in a Bottle
episodes.overview: When Lana responds emotionally to a message in a bottle, a jealous Lyle tries his own hand at romantic poetry.

episodes.name: Fame, Fortune, Madness
episodes.overview: J.P. Weasel makes a return visit to Freeborn, and everyone is understandably suspicious of the charlatan. Still, in no time at all, our gang falls for his promises of fame and fortune, hook, line and sinker.

episodes.name: Storyteller
episodes.overview: Lyle falls asleep reading Robin Hood, and dreams the romantic tale starring himself and Lana.

episodes.name: Animal Court
episodes.overview: When no one will admit to theft, it's decided by Lana that the mystery can only be solved in a Freeborn courtroom.

episodes.name: Boo
episodes.overview: Freeborn is haunted! What starts out as a playful sting on Lyle ends up scaring everybody.

episodes.name: Fountain of Youth
episodes.overview: The gang believes one of their ponds has magically transformed into a fountain of youth.

episodes.name: Brand New Gnu
episodes.overview: Gnu falls out of a tree, and forgetting who he is, accidently assumes the identity of his son's favourite comic character.

episodes.name: Boyz Night Out
episodes.overview: Little Louie decides to go out on an adventure all by himself, provoking Lyle and the others to form a hapless search party.

episodes.name: Fools Gold
episodes.overview: Lyle finds what he believes to be a treasure map, and the gang combines all their natural tracking instincts to find it.

episodes.name: Near Myths
episodes.overview: Our gang, ever-ready to believe anything, gets caught up trying to debunk a ridiculous succession of urban myths.
